<document>
	<title>Nasal aspects of cystic fibrosis in children.</title>

	<author>Berman-J-M.</author>
	<author>Colman-B-H.</author>

	<source>J-Laryngol-Otol. 1977 Feb. 91(2). P 133-9.</source>

	<abstract>Despite the extraordinary prevalence of upper respiratory allergy and
   infection in children nasal polyposis is an extremely rare condition.
   Seven cases of cystic fibrosis are presented in order to demonstrate
   the nasal aspects of the disease. All but one had nasal polyposis.
   The literature has been reviewed with particular reference to
   clinical, radiological and histo-pathological features. Conservative
   treatment is stressed.</abstract>

